upset jill, though.

16:49.708 --> 16:52.843
She thinks I'm only charming
for other people and not her.

16:52.844 --> 16:55.345
Oh. Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

16:55.346 --> 16:59.583
I think she wants things
to be like they were
when we first met.

16:59.584 --> 17:01.518
But I like the way
things are now.

17:01.519 --> 17:04.989
I like not always having
to impress the other person
or get dressed up.

17:04.990 --> 17:07.625
Mm-hmm. So you
would tend to agree
with j.B. Priestley,

17:07.626 --> 17:11.729
Who said that, "marriage
is like an endless visit
in your worst clothes."

17:11.730 --> 17:13.463
<i>(chuckles)</i>

17:13.464 --> 17:15.799
That guy really knew
about marriage.

17:15.800 --> 17:18.969
And divorce, too.
He was married three times.

17:18.970 --> 17:21.137
Oh, no!

17:21.138 --> 17:23.507
Three mother-in-laws.
<i>(clucks)</i>

17:23.508 --> 17:25.474
<i>(laughs)</i>

17:25.476 --> 17:27.911
When jill and I
first got married,

17:27.912 --> 17:30.848
In order win her, I really
had to pour on the charm.

17:30.849 --> 17:33.583
Then she wanted to
see through the charm and
see if I really loved her.

17:33.584 --> 17:37.154
And now that she knows
I really love her,
she wants the charm back.

17:37.155 --> 17:41.391
Hmm. Well, tim,
maybe after 15 years
of marriage,

17:41.392 --> 17:46.363
Making an effort
to be more charming
has more meaning.

17:46.364 --> 17:48.398
Hmm. Yeah.

17:48.399 --> 17:51.969
It's too bad.
I like being comfortable
in my own house.

17:51.970 --> 17:55.539
If I've got a little gas,
I don't want to have to run out
to the backyard.

17:57.308 --> 17:59.543
I don't want that, either.

18:08.186 --> 18:10.420
Jill?
Hi.

18:11.823 --> 18:14.391
Hi. I was laying under
the hot rod,

18:14.392 --> 18:16.526
And I got to thinking
about you.

18:16.527 --> 18:19.563
Really? Usually
you're laying with me

18:19.564 --> 18:22.299
And get to thinking
about the hot rod.

18:24.602 --> 18:26.636
I think you're right.

18:26.637 --> 18:30.040
I don't really work on
charming you like I used to.

18:30.041 --> 18:31.809
Well, that's true.

18:31.810 --> 18:36.146
I don't think
you wore coveralls to bed
until the fifth anniversary.

18:36.147 --> 18:40.383
I just don't wanna
be one of those priests that
drops eggs on his three wives.

18:44.655 --> 18:45.923
What?

18:49.060 --> 18:53.296
Sometimes in a marriage,
you can get too comfortable.

18:53.297 --> 18:56.166
Well, we're both
getting lazy.

18:56.167 --> 18:59.770
I guess after 15 years
and three kids,
it's kinda natural.

18:59.771 --> 19:03.340
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
But I don't wanna get so lazy
that we stop trying.

19:03.341 --> 19:05.642
Me neither.

19:05.643 --> 19:08.078
Do you remember
when I asked you to marry me?

19:08.079 --> 19:11.281
I was so nervous, my hands
were as sweaty as toilets.

19:16.955 --> 19:19.189
Why were you nervous?

19:19.190 --> 19:22.159
I was afraid you'd say no
and I'd have to spend
the rest of my life without you.

19:22.160 --> 19:24.094
I knew I couldn't
return that ring.

19:26.430 --> 19:28.766
You still make me laugh.

19:28.767 --> 19:32.435
That's good.
It's the best 15 years
I've ever had.

19:39.844 --> 19:43.247
Got a little gift for you.
Stay right there.

19:43.248 --> 19:45.382
Oh...

19:47.752 --> 19:50.087
You still have
some charm left.

19:50.088 --> 19:52.355
I still have some tricks
up my sleeve.

20:04.803 --> 20:07.470
Whoa!

20:07.471 --> 20:09.873
Bond. James bond.

20:13.744 --> 20:17.214
<i>(â™ª "the way you look tonight")</i>

20:21.485 --> 20:24.521
I wish that I had
a beautiful gown on
underneath my robe.

20:24.522 --> 20:27.424
What do you have on
under there?
Nothing.

20:27.425 --> 20:28.792
Ohh-ho.

20:31.095 --> 20:33.063
That's better than any gown.

20:58.323 --> 21:02.125
Are mom and dad up yet?
No. And quit bugging us!

21:02.126 --> 21:04.728
It's late. When are they
gonna get up?

21:04.729 --> 21:06.529
Don't you know anything?

21:06.530 --> 21:08.565
Whenever mom and dad
have a fight,

21:08.566 --> 21:12.336
Dad apologizes,
and then, the next morning,
they sleep late.

21:14.038 --> 21:17.174
I don't think
they're sleeping.

21:17.175 --> 21:21.011
You don't? Why not?

21:21.012 --> 21:24.647
Because I heard them
jumping up and down
on their bed.

21:26.351 --> 21:28.518
Oh... Well, you know,

21:28.519 --> 21:32.522
They're probably
just having one of their,
um... Somersault contests.

21:34.492 --> 21:37.427
Yeah. It's a lot like
the olympics.

21:38.729 --> 21:41.698
Sounds like fun.
Why don't they ask us to play?

21:44.468 --> 21:47.905
Trust me, mark.
You don't wanna play.

21:51.276 --> 21:53.676
Oh. Hi, mom. Hi, dad.

21:53.677 --> 21:57.714
Hi, sweetie.
What a great day.

21:57.715 --> 22:00.250
Yeah, what a great day.
Yeah.

22:01.719 --> 22:04.021
Brad and randy told me
what you were doing upstairs.

22:08.293 --> 22:10.227
They did?

22:10.228 --> 22:14.864
Yeah. Having one of those
somersault contests. Who won?

22:15.934 --> 22:19.036
Your mom won.
She always wins.

22:25.476 --> 22:28.178
You did win, didn't you?
Twice.

22:28.179 --> 22:29.646
<i>(grunts)</i>

22:33.751 --> 22:36.420
Does everybody know
what time it is?

22:39.424 --> 22:42.960
Ok, there's a little thing
we do here. We yell "tool time."

22:44.528 --> 22:46.930
It sounds like
you've given this
a lot of thought.

22:46.931 --> 22:48.865
Well, we had three...
Three babies...

22:48.866 --> 22:51.368
When the boys were babies,
and I... You know...

22:53.771 --> 22:56.039
Men are actually
a lot like babies.
